I"<p>CGPGrey has a great video about new-years resoloutions and why they dont work, and insted suggestes that we use a theme. So for example somone who wants to improve there eduction might have a theme of learning. This is broad enough to keep you on track but not shackel you to somthing like a resoloution like <em>I will read 2 books a month</em> because that goal is easy to fail and hard to get back on once you do. With a theme you have a guiding light to pull you towards where you want to be. Most actions that you take should have a moment of consideration <em>Will this take me closer to X theme</em> and if yes you should do them and if no you should think if they are worth the other benefits.</p>

